For the latest GA release ST please check [here](https://support.rightscale.com/12-Guides/RightLink10).

Base ServerTemplate for RightLink10. RightLink10 is a new agent to connect servers to the RightScale platform that is very lightweight and simple to install.
_It is not a plug-in upgrade from the older RightLink v6 series._
See [https://support.rightscale.com/12-Guides/RightLink10](https://support.rightscale.com/12-Guides/RightLink10) for details.

This base ST runs an init script to update the packaging system and enable automatic security updates, and a collectd script to install the RightScale monitoring (based on collectd v4). The source of this ST is available at [https://github.com/rightscale/rightlink_scripts/tree/10.0.rc4](https://github.com/rightscale/rightlink_scripts/tree/10.0.rc4).

The base ST can run on most any Linux distro that supports cloud-init. The monitoring is currently known to work on Ubuntu 14.04, Ubuntu 12.04, CentOS 6, CentOS 7, RedHat 6.5, and RedHat 7. It is recommended to use the standard distro images in various clouds. In order to load RL10 at boot time the MCIs (or the servers) need to be tagged with:
 - `rs_agent:mime_include_url=https://rightlinklite.rightscale.com/rll/10.0.rc4/rightlink.boot.sh`
 - `rs_agent:type=right_link_lite`

Support for this ServerTemplate comes directly through product/engineering for select customers, it is not currently supported through the regular RightScale support channels.","name":"RightLink 10.0.rc4 Linux Base","lineage":"https://us-3.rightscale.com/api/acct/60073/ec2_server_templates/348626003"}]
